WHEREAS, returning starters Graham Ashby, Colt Bryan, Colby Groce, and Lawrence
Guthrie all earned recognition on the All-Conference, All-Area, and All-Sectional teams; after
being the sixth man on Unity's 2023-2024 Sweet Sixteen team, Samuel Bryan ascended to the
starting lineup and without fail had huge performances in the season's most important games
and moments; and
WHEREAS, the other varsity Lions who excelled on the court during this championship
season included eighth graders Will Byrd, Lawson Honey, Beau Watt, and Brody Wilson;
seventh graders Jayce Jean and Hezzie Phelps; and sixth grader Maddox Groce; and
WHEREAS, junior varsity Lions Beau Bradford, Silas Bryan, Fletcher Byrd, Lincoln
Caldwell, Heath Cunningham, Bentley Eakes, Silas Fugate, Garrett Marks, Walker McCain, and
Jed Watt also earned the title of state champions by pushing their varsity teammates daily in
practice and bringing remarkable sideline energy in games; and
WHEREAS, the Lions were led by Coach Stephen Bryan, whose calm demeanor, in-
game adjustments, conditioning sessions, and inbounds-play wizardry were the stuff of legend;
and
WHEREAS, under Coach Bryan, Principal Bridgette Jones, Assistant Principal Carrie
Bradford, and Athletics Director Jennifer Medley, the Lions have grown not only as leaders on
the basketball court but throughout their community, where they prominently serve in the Unity
Student Council, Fellowship of Christian Athletes, and Beta Club and are key members of the
baseball, football, Scholars' Bowl, soccer, and tennis teams; and
WHEREAS, the Lions were empowered by remarkable support from their community,
who traveled en masse to every postseason game and filled the gymnasium at the state
tournament in Murfreesboro; and
WHEREAS, during this incredible season, the members of the Unity Lions etched their
names into the annals of Tennessee sports history, and the character, perseverance,
